1️⃣1️⃣ DataLoader (Fix N+1 Problem)

N+1 Problem: If fetching users and their posts → one query per user.

Solution: DataLoader batches queries.

Example:

const DataLoader = require('dataloader');

const postLoader = new DataLoader(async (userIds) => {
  const posts = await db.getPostsByUserIds(userIds);
  return userIds.map(id => posts.filter(p => p.userId === id));
});

Resolver:

User: {
  posts: (parent, args, context) => {
    return context.postLoader.load(parent.id);
  }
}

This batches all requests into one DB call.


---

1️⃣2️⃣ Schema Stitching & Federation

Schema Stitching

Combines multiple GraphQL services into one.

Federation (Microservices Architecture)

Developed by Apollo GraphQL.

Allows multiple services to own part of the schema.

Example:

Service A:

type User @key(fields: "id") {
  id: ID!
  name: String!
}

Service B:

extend type User @key(fields: "id") {
  id: ID! @external
  posts: [Post]
}

Gateway combines them.


