🔥 1️⃣ Explain the N+1 Problem in GraphQL. How do you solve it?

Problem

When resolving nested fields, GraphQL may execute one query per parent record.

Example:

query {
  users {
    id
    posts {
      title
    }
  }
}

If there are 100 users:

1 query → fetch users

100 queries → fetch posts for each user


Total = 101 queries ❌


---

Solution → Use DataLoader

Batch and cache database calls.

const DataLoader = require('dataloader');

const postLoader = new DataLoader(async (userIds) => {
  const posts = await db.getPostsByUserIds(userIds);
  return userIds.map(id =>
    posts.filter(post => post.userId === id)
  );
});

Resolver:

User: {
  posts: (parent, args, context) => {
    return context.postLoader.load(parent.id);
  }
}

Now:

1 query → users

1 query → posts (batched)


Total = 2 queries ✅


