🔥 3️⃣ What are Resolvers? How does execution work internally?

GraphQL resolves fields depth-first.

Example Query:

query {
  user(id: "1") {
    name
    posts {
      title
    }
  }
}

Execution order:

1. Query.user


2. User.name


3. User.posts


4. Post.title



Each field has its own resolver.

Resolver signature:

(fieldParent, args, context, info)

parent → result from previous resolver

args → arguments passed

context → shared data (auth, DB)

info → query metadata



