🧠 4️⃣ GraphQL Gateway Layer (Federation)

This is the brain of the architecture.

At scale, we don’t use a single monolithic server. We use Federation via Apollo GraphQL Gateway.

Responsibilities:

Combine multiple service schemas

Route queries to appropriate services

Merge responses

Enforce auth rules

Apply query depth limits

Handle tracing



---

Example Federation Flow

Client Query:

query {
  order(id: "1") {
    id
    user {
      name
    }
    products {
      name
      price
    }
  }
}

Gateway Execution:

1. Call Order Service → get order data


2. Call User Service → resolve user


3. Call Product Service → resolve products


4. Merge response


5. Return unified JSON



Client sees ONE API. Internally → multiple services.


